Factors Affecting Star Ratings of Juices Bars & Smoothies Stalls

alextan2468
14-Nov-2015

Introduction

  • Many “Juice Bars & Smoothies” stalls seem popular and profitable in the city I live. Hence the motivation to study why some stalls have high star ratings while some do not.
  • Understand key success factors => Start profitable ($$$) juice/smoothie stalls in future!!!
  • What I did with “Juice Bars & Smoothies” subset of Yelp data:
    • Analyze the attributes and categories in the Business data set for relation to ratings.
    • Analyze the text in the Review data set for relation of ratings to sentiment on various aspects of the customer experience.

Methodology Used

  • Business data set analysis:
    • Business attributes are multi-levels factors and explored using box plots. Student T-test (2-sided with 5% significance level) was attempted too to confirm the significance.
    • Business categories are numerous (60 categories) and only 2 levels per category (T/F correspond to belonging to the category or not), analyzed using Fisher Tests.
  • Review data set analysis:
    • Topic terms & phrase extraction: Frequent terms were gleaned from Word Cloud created from review text and clustered into 4 main topic groups. Each review text entry was split into phrases which were extracted for sentiment analysis if topic words exist in the phrases.
    • Sentiment analysis: Jeffrey Breen's approach used. It is a simple word search sentiment classification based on an Opinion Lexicon (Hu & Liu's). (https://sites.google.com/site/miningtwitter/questions/sentiment/analysis)

Key Insight From Business Data Set

  • Hard business attributes seem no correlation to star ratings with the key exception of Price
  • Takeaway: Want to avoid low ratings on Yelp? Benchmark market prices (Price ranges 1 & 2) and not set them too high (Price Range 3,4).

Key Insight From Review Data Set

  • Word cloud of reviews show topic words revolve around 3 other key aspects other than Price, namely: Drink, Food, Service, with (surprise!) Food being as dominant as Drink.

  • Takeaway 1: Consider having a menu of great tasting food to complement the drinks.
  • Takeaway 2: Provide great tasting juices & food at reasonable prices and with good service attitude is key to high star ratings.
